node.title: Cullasaja Fog
node.description: It was tough to get  a great shot during this morning on Highway 64, but the clouds parted just enough for me to see the falls.  This is the cliche shot of Cullasaja Falls but a hard one to pass up each time I'm in the area.  One day I look forward to having more time and finding a "new" shot......

node.title: This Old Barn
node.description: I've driven past this barn in Franklin, NC numerous times.  Glad I finally stopped.

node.title: Quarry Falls Wide Angle
node.description: From a recent trip to Franklin, NC.  This is a portion of the Cullasaja River and Quarry Falls (Bust your butt Falls) on Highway 64.  Struggled with the sun all day long, but found a little cloud cover to get this shot in.

node.title: Devil's Den
node.description: One of the Upper Falls at Devil's Den

node.title: Shhhhhhhh
node.description: Able to get up to Cheaha with a good friend this weekend.  After being inspired by many of my contacts to "work for the shot," I think spent more time in the water than out this trip. This is one of the crystal clear cascades of Devil's Den along the Chinnabee Silent Trail.  Hit the "L" on your keypad.
